Title: THE EMOJI MOVIE - Official Trailer (HD)
Comment:
I'm seeing a lot of people comment "You can't complain too much about these films, they're for kids", I have to counter argue this defence with these points:


1) The term "It's a kids' movie" can defend why a film isn't too violent or why it has a colourful art style, but it shouldn't be used to explain why a film is bad, children's films aren't immune from criticism and "It's a Kids' movie" isn't a license for a film to be lazy or uncreative.


2) The Default acceptable standard for children's movies shouldn't be "Whatever, it'll do, it's for kids", especially when there's so many children's movies out there that are both emotionally challenging and imaginative, from "Toy Story" to "The Secret of NIMH", "Matilda" to "The Neverending Story", there's no excuses for children's films to get away with being insultingly low standard or unambitious. 


3) Children aren't the only audience who watch these films, don't forget that parents have to see them too, why should it be a chore or punishment for them? Give them an experience that they can appreciate with their kids, a bonding opportunity that they can sincerely share.


Great children's movies respect their young audience, they don't underestimate what kids can take in as an audience, they believe that kids are smarter than we think and try to teach them to understand storytelling values, they are so well written & produced that they can be treasured for a lifetime. Let's not shrug our shoulders or turn the other cheek when a film for kids is bad, we need to call them out on their low standards or easy pandering, because the next generation deserve movies that treat them with respect and don't just see them as a money making opportunity.

Title: THE EMOJI MOVIE - Official Trailer (HD)
Comment:
For those of you who defend this movie by saying that it‚Äôs a kids movie, here are the list of reasons as to why this movie is bad for kids: 

Gene and Jailbreak's stories essentially cancel each other out, message-wise. One wants to conform and learns to value freedom, while another wants freedom and ends up conforming. This is especially ironic considering that the main focus was about Gene learning to reject the oppressive caste system and express himself, instead of just performing his one function.

Wisecrack Edition made the case that the lesson of "you should reject societal expectations and express who you truly wish to be" couldn't escape unbroken. Sure, Smiler was defeated and the Emojis learn that it's perfectly fine to express more than one emotion. However, there is still the fact that they are stuck with one ''function'', to serve Alex. Emojis were invented for this very specific purpose, so Textopolis is a terrible metaphor. The movie constantly validates the idea that they should only peruse society's intended purpose for them. In Real Life, the pressure to conform can easily prevent people from being themselves.

If emojis wanted to become more than merely vessels of conveying ideas or express whatever they feel, then Alex could simply delete them as they would have outlived their usefulness. After all, Gene didn't stop the phone from being erased. It was Alex who stopped it because his crush was so Easily Impressed, and the movie fails to call him out for attempting to delete the phone data.

Aspects of the caste system still remain intact as the unpopular emojis remain in the Loser Lounge.

Jailbreak learns to stop valuing her freedom and reverts back to being a Princess.

Gene quickly discards the idea of leaving the phone forever.

Hi-5 never dumps his narcissistic ways to become a more well rounded emoji.

For a movie where women have "limitless potential" there don't seem to be any interestingly written female characters. The only female emojis we see with major speaking roles are Smiler, a generic order obsessed villain who runs society like a dictator, a generic princess, Jailbreak, a Jerkass who accomplishes nothing except breaking Gene's heart, and the generic love interest. There is also Gene's mother Mary, who's little more than a particularly emotionless Extreme Doormat and Akiko Glitter, who's a genuine Nice Girl but who is so expendable that our hero Gene leaves her to die in the trash can. Note that the most significant female character other than the villain, Jailbreak fits three out of those six characteristics. And it gets even worse outside of the phone, where Addie is merely a Satellite Love Interest with less character than the emojis.

If Jailbreak is meant to be a strong independent-minded female role model, then why does she learn to fit in with the same societal expectations that she found sexist? It seems to suggest that you can only save the day by following tradition, since revealing herself as a princess is treated as an empowering moment. And why does the movie treat her as being incredibly selfish for rejecting Gene's fairy-tale views of romance?

The fact that it's the male character who learns to value freedom while the female character who learns to conform and become a potential love interest also sends uncomfortable implications about a woman's place in the world...

Also, Jailbreak's heavy-handed rants about women being denied positions of power and the ability to voice their own ideas seems at least a little misplaced when you realize that Smiler, the leader of the Emojis, is female! It actually makes Jailbreak's inability to achieve a high position in life seem like a product of her own Jerk Assery, incompetence, and unwillingness to conform to standards, rather than the product of a "broken system", and makes it seem like she's just whining and making excuses. This has the very unfortunate effect of implying the same about people in real life who complain about the Glass Ceiling...

Even throwing in a lesson about Real Women Don't Wear Dresses undermines the Be Yourself Aesop because it involves defining your life in opposition to gender roles, rather than accepting a unique identity of your own that includes a variety of traits.

Jailbreak's cred as a sophisticated hacker falls significantly short of what the movie wants us to believe what she can do. Despite her claims to be strong and independent, she almost falls to her death (in Just Dance, of all places) and her two displays of "hacking" in the movie (guessing the password to a firewall and deprogramming the bot that's trying to kill Gene) are both upstaged by Hi-5, of all people. Conversely, her only noteworthy accomplishment happens when she embraces her princess side and whistles for the Twitter logo, accidentally suggesting she was better off as a stereotype.

If the movie was supposed to mock and critique excessive use of technology, then this is sure as hell broken when the simple act of sending a text ultimately saves the day. Also, because we don't get to see the real problems that it causes, none of the human characters learn the drawbacks of their obsession with smartphones. For their lack of trying, the movie just makes this behaviour seem normal.

Hi-5 has to learn to stop being a narcissistic jerk and learn the value of having true friends. Yet he still yearns for popularity through the entire movie. Shortly after he comes back and says he learned his lesson, he shouts about how "they love us" without any humility whatsoever. He presumably reverts back to being a jerk. To make matters worse, he got along with Gene just fine and they were able to work together to accomplish their own goals, suggesting that narcissism doesn't really harm your relationships and life goals.

The message about being a supportive father is undermined since Mel changed his mind and believed that his son was ready for the prime time, yet his doubts were correct since Gene got Stage Fright on his very first day. The movie calls him out for not being supportive, yet a good parent would understand their child's strengths and weaknesses so that they can help them succeed.

The theme of Emoji prejudice against Gene is pushed hard to represent the struggles of the LGBT community, according to Word of God... but Gene actually experiences very little Fantastic Racism when he's just walking through the streets of Textopolis making various faces - the other emojis on the street seem to either like him or not care about his transgressions. Society actually allowed him to have a chance to use his talents, and he failed miserably. The only time he does get treated with major hostility is when he screws up majorly on the job in a way that puts the entire phone in danger which, honestly, is fair.

People like The Mysterious Mr. Enter have made the case that even the blatant Product Placement falls flat. Emojis are so great at communicating ideas that a normal emoji would be insufficient to communicate the basic idea of love. The main message of Be Yourself makes little sense when it comes to technology, because customers want smartphones that follow their commands, not for the apps to be whatever they want to be. The only reason that Textopolis was spared from destruction was because Gene glitched out when he was placed on the pedestal at the end, something that the creators of these apps want to avoid at all costs.

Title: THE EMOJI MOVIE - Official Trailer (HD)
Comment:
I'm seeing a lot of people comment "You can't complain too much about these films, they're for kids", I have to counter argue this defence with these points:


1) The term "It's a kids' movie" can defend why a film isn't too violent or why it has a colourful art style, but it shouldn't be used to explain why a film is bad, children's films aren't immune from criticism and "It's a Kids' movie" isn't a license for a film to be lazy or uncreative.


2) The Default acceptable standard for children's movies shouldn't be "Whatever, it'll do, it's for kids", especially when there's so many children's movies out there that are both emotionally challenging and imaginative, from "Toy Story" to "The Secret of NIMH", "Matilda" to "The Neverending Story", there's no excuses for children's films to get away with being insultingly low standard or unambitious. 


3) Children aren't the only audience who watch these films, don't forget that parents have to see them too, why should it be a chore or punishment for them? Give them an experience that they can appreciate with their kids, a bonding opportunity that they can sincerely share.


Great children's movies respect their young audience, they don't underestimate what kids can take in as an audience, they believe that kids are smarter than we think and try to teach them to understand storytelling values, they are so well written & produced that they can be treasured for a lifetime. Let's not shrug our shoulders or turn the other cheek when a film for kids is bad, we need to call them out on their low standards or easy pandering, because the next generation deserve movies that treat them with respect and don't just see them as a money making opportunity, thank you.

Title: THE EMOJI MOVIE - Official Trailer (HD)
Comment:
This movie is so diverse.
The message really is dependet on the reciever.
(SPOILER ALERT AHEAD)
 You could be a toddler and focus on the music and the colors.
 You could be a child and just focus on the poop and fart jokes with the dancy feelings on most of the music parts
 You could be a teen and focus on the story and follow along.
 You could also be an adult and get the small hints of sex jokes and so on.
But if you think about every scene  twice, everything changes
Disney told us a wonderfull message, if you haven't figured it out yet, i'm here to enlighten you.

At the beginning of the movie, it was set during high school, the Gen-Z's that were mostly relying on techs and gadgets. Thus setting up the enviroment.

Then we got introduced to Gene.
A different emoji in a world were differencials are unacceptable, his parents like-wise.
This could be applied into real life.
He then tries to fit in, he want to fit in and so began the journey to find Jailbreak and make him "normal"

On the way we got to know that Gene has a great personality, friends first was one of the more shallow messages but the more important message came later.

The journey they went on. Hi-five, Gene and Jailbreak's trip was astounding, thus Gene caught feelings for jailbreak.

Jailbreak rejected him at the end and the happy ending was on the horizon.

The message was as true as ever.
You grow up getting told to be same as everyone else, no exceptions, group pressure is a fact and normality is a law.
You try to change yourself for someone you love, someone you befriend with and the groups you're hanging out with.
And along the way, you'll have difficulties, deppresion and feeling outside is a fact among us teens (i know it's foward but it's true)
And so you get a lifesaver.
The one in a million that helps you trought everything, in this case it was Jailbreak and Hi-Five.
This livesaver is almost 100% the opposite sex.
You go trought hell together and fall in love, getting rejected is common and eventually you get to see the harsh reality and the consenquence of being different.
You give that up and fall amongst the normal's. (When he became a meh in the end)
But things go bright in the end, everyone embraced his differences and things went north.
The thing is, no matter how different you are.
Don't give it up to fit in
Cause in the end, you might just be the one that is "Normal"

Feel free to comment if i missed any important messages in the movie, hope you'll see this movie as an enlightment and not just an another disney-filler movies.

Title: THE EMOJI MOVIE - Official Trailer (HD)
Comment: As a nine year old, I can honestly say that this movie is TERRIBLE. I've seen a lot of people in the comments saying things like "THIS MOVIE WAS TARGETED FOR 5-11 YEAR OLDS SO STOP HATING ON IT" but, in reality there are so many things wrong with it and pretty obviously was made for money. I'm not stupid, ok? This movie has SO MANY advertisements "hidden" within it, it seems like they just don't care anymore! Also, they add absolutely NO LOGIC to this story at all! It's fine to have an amount of fantasy in your story, but at least don't make tons of plotholes just because it's easier.. The characters are just awful, they don't seem to have any personality. Take Alex for example, he's just extremely locked up inside his smartphone, and all he wants to do is impress a girl he likes. However, not by using words, but THROUGH EMOJIS. The emojis "just wanna fit in"... sound familiar? It's the most chlich√© storyline ever. Also, they try to sneak in adult jokes. I have absolutely no idea why, but they just do it. One example is, when a conversation came up about love, our favorite Hi-5 emoji said "When a peace sign only gave me only one finger,  I knew she was in love with me". What the heck?! Why are they referencing the middle finger?! There are just SO many terrible poop puns, and it seems like they just expected people to let them slide. All in all, this movie is very flawed and I can see why people don't like it. I'm disappointed in what you expect kids to consider quality content. Sony Pictures Animation, I know you can do better than this. Sure, say all you want about "YOU couldn't make a movie this good" or something like that, because you're right, I couldn't. I just know Sony Pictures is capable of making things much better than this, because I do enjoy most of their movies. Sorry if I offended you, and I won't criticize you for enjoying this movie. This is just my vision of this film, so if you have a constructive opinion about it, please tell me and I will take it into deep consideration. Thanks.

The Alpha Generation is going to be in ¬†(I'm the class of 2021, so I don't have some ways to say this,) more use of technology, and that they don't go outside as much as the generation of the 2000 year's. This relates to the movie by presenting the problem, along with qoutes from Ironic characters. The main character Genetically programmed to be a "Meh" emoji does not fullfill his purpose, sent into exile, found his true love, able to express other emoji's such as the "Heart Eyes" emoji, the shy emoji, etc. In other sense, it is a well rounded movie and created by Sony Pictures Entertainment. It is a good movie showing the theme as "Express yourself and do not be afraid of limiting yourself because of what other people think." It is a child's theme but a good one sense it does make it kid friendly. If only the people actually watched the movie, looking it up I have found that 30% of the people who rated it rated it good while the other 70% did not. I can bet my life that more than a 1/4 of that 70% hasn't watched the movie seeing that it is bad from other people. I like the movie and it's use of music, it really did change the main character's perspective. Although it was a 1 hour 31 minute long. If changed to be longer, it will be better to fullfill the character's background. Please take this into consideration because I do not agree with the people who has not watched the movie but claims it's bad in sorts of ways. I like it, and that is my claim.

Yes this is a movie meant for children but the problem is it is only meant for children. What happened to movies that both parents and children can enjoy like wall-e, Finding Nemo, Toy Story 1,2 and 3 those movies are movies that I can enjoy watching in the cinemas with my kids. During the time I was watching the emoji movie it was clear that the only one that was enjoying the movie was my kid and he's 10 years old. If you wanna make an animated movie please make one for both parents and children to enjoy for example the new Pixar movie Coco which was really good because it managed capture my attention with its strong message about family and tradition. From now on I'm just gonna watch Pixar movies with my kids.

Comment:
I am the messenger. I speak for the Internet.

The Internet was not appeased by The Emoji Movie, Sony Pictures Entertainment.

The Internet predicts you will crumble into a thousand pieces.

However, the Internet says that your fall will be slow and agonizing.

There will be 5 Disasters.

The First Disaster will that your movie will be widely hated and the haters' opinions will be spread through a 100 websites, including Instagram, YouTube, Facebook, Snapchat and many more.

The Second Disaster will occur when people will stop buying your products and your TVs will be useless.

The Third Disaster will be when your company splits in half with your animation studio splitting from your network over profits.

The Forth Disaster will be when Sony Pictures Animation shuts down due to bankruptcy and bad, low profitable animated movies like The Emoji Movie.

The Fifth and final Disaster will be when your company shuts down completely, also sharing the same fate as your animation studio.

The Internet says your DOOMED, unless you shut down your animation studio and completely destroy all of it's movies. Leave no remains.¬†

Do not attack or sue me, Sony Pictures Entertainment, I only speak for the Internet......... ( Even though I hate The Emoji Movie as well ).

Title: THE EMOJI MOVIE - Official Trailer (HD)
Comment:
The movie has a cool and unique idea, was cute and had some nice jokes, BUUUUT...

I'm sorry, but WHY! Why do the messages this movie wants to pedal have to be so obvious...

Why does she explicitly have to say "I'm not a princess waiting for her prince" or "Men always get credit for women's ideas" ? 

Take Lion King for example, when was the exact moment in the movie where Nala said "I'm a strong lioness and I'm gonna be brave, cause female lions are just as brave and strong as male lions and I'm going to fight and bring back the true King!" ???

Doesn't it sound ridiculous ? How great it is, that it was subtle, incorporated in the story to MAKE SENSE and not in your fucking face, retarded, completely unreal dialogue ?

Yeah we get it, the girl doesn't want to be a princess, she wants to be a hacker. Great! What's the problem in just exploring the character and have the audience understand her through her actions and feelings instead of, again IN YOUR FUCKING FACE, words that no sensible person says EVER ???

Social agendas ruin movies, the same way there are no actually well done movies about religion... There is no subtlety, no nuance and aaaall the points need to be hammered in the eyes and ears of the viewers without any actual artistic substance. Just dry political messages slapped on animations... Pathetic...

All the emojis live in a world where they can express whatever emotion they want, but every time a human texts and uses an emoji, giant mechanical hands rain down from the sky and grabs however many emojis the human uses for that particular text. Title: THE EMOJI MOVIE - Official Trailer (HD)
Comment:
I watched this movie and even the kids in the theatre seemed to be bored! So I made a list of OTHER movies you can show young ones, corresponding to reasons you might want to see this one. My rule of thumb: If the movie is too bad for you to sit through, don't show it to kids! 

Suggestions:
Bright colors and fun visuals: wreck-it-Ralph, Ponyo, The Little Mermaid, Inside Out
Things that explore technology that they like: wreck-it-Ralph
Funny movies: This'll be different depending on your kids. Different kids have different senses of humour! Try out some Pixar films, find what your kids like. Personally I laughed a lot at Inside Out and Kung Fu Panda
Different worlds: wreck-it-Ralph, Cars 1 and 3, Finding Nemo
Everyday objects that ARE different worlds: Toy Story
General recommendations: Moana, Up, Cats Don't Dance
My favorites as a kid: The Iron Giant, Spirited Away, Finding Nemo, 101 Dalmatians, Land Before Time, How To Train Your Dragon

Point being: There are plenty of movies kids will like that don't insult their intelligence! Disney is a good place to start, but look into other ones too; different companies like Studio Ghibli turn out interesting movies that your kids might like to see too. Understand when kids are distracted versus kids having legit fun. Also account for what your kids like!

TIP:
The movies I have suggested are not showing in cinemas, but if your kids really love the experience, some cinemas do summer matinee or kids' group showings of Disney films (for reduced prices to boot!). Don't be afraid to ask the local cinema if they do this! 

Have a good day!

Title: THE EMOJI MOVIE - Official Trailer (HD)
Comment:
The emoji movie is this summers top movie. It follows three main characters, gene, jailbreak and hi-5 as they journey to the cloud. Gene is a special emoji who is gifted with multiple emotions in a world where you can't be different, he meets up with our supporting characters to become what he must be, a meh. They run into many complications and grow as characters.

I don't understand the hate surrounding this movie and frankly I'm insulted and confused why anybody would feel that way, I thought it was a masterpiece in every sense of the word. I couldn't stop laughing throughout the duration of the film. I enjoyed it incredibly. It was immersing, I related to every character on a deep emotional level, the main character Gene (played by famous actor T J Miller) seemed to grow so much and by the end it was like seeing the achievements of my own child. I loved the strong female character, it was great to see feminism portrayed I such a great way. Hi-5 was so funny and his design was humorous.

Now let me tell you about the plot. This movie was deep, I found myself completely immersed and time seemed to fly. By the end I felt like a different person, this is so much more then a children's movie. I'd recommend to anybody to go see this movie. It seems like it will become a classic like pulp fiction or back to the future in no time. And trust me when I say, I've already got tickets to see it again. 

Over all I would give this movie a 9/10 and I'm a pretty tough critic. So make sure you get your tickets now and prepare for the best movie you'll see in a while. By the end you won't be going meh! ;)

Comment:
Sony Pictures Entertainment
Sony, Sony, Sony. I look forward to tearing this movie apart when i get the chance. This films existence is the epitome of everything wrong and horrible about the film industry. I hope this movie bombs as fast as Pluto Nash and The Groovenians. This movie has a 0% rating on rotten tomatoes. I hope this film kills Sony Animation as a film studio. This movie is a complete ripoff of Wreck It Ralph, a much, much more respectable film. Just think Sony, this is the second summer in a row that one of your films has been ripped to shreds before it even came out. Just think. You could have done the Popeye film, and i guarantee that it wouldn't have nearly this many dislikes. This movie has more hate than I think Ghostbusters did. At least that movie had an excuse, since it was in development hell for years. This film is simply corporate pandering bullshit, that i can guarantee will NOT be a financial OR critical success. You can do so much better Sony, if only you actually put forth some effort.

On this day, something unspeakable was unleashed.. *[Play dead island trailer theme]*
It was just a normal Thursday, everyone woke up, got dressed, and headed down to breakfast. Many brewed a cup of coffee, some may have even grabbed a glass of water.

Sitting them selves down, they begin to browse the web as they wake up. Scrolling through the news, they fly by something, only to freeze. Sliding the phone screen back up, they see it. 

....


*The Emoji Movie*

They begin to gag, choking for air as they hit the kitchen floor with a swift 'thud'. They lay there quietly, watching outside their windows as their life force fades away.

This same behavior spreads globally, dropping earths population soon into the hundreds. As the numbers drop fast, only one individual remains.

This last young man wakes up, only to find the entire world dead. He sits there, complelty in shock.
With his head in his hands, he receives a 'beep' from his phone. Looking up, he grabs it, swipping at the lock screen. Seeing the caption appear, he knows what he must do.

But before he attempts to take his own life, the phone dies. Leaving him in a petrified silence.

He had been watching to much porn the night prior, so his phone battery drained. 

As this realization kicks in, he lets out a shout of anger. 

"CURSE YOU PORN HUB!"

The camera pans out of the house, up into the sky, and fades to black.


                        *The End*

2020: The Movie Movie 

It's about a man name Steve who works as a post-production supervisor at SONY(He Hates his job). He has a friend named Michael that wants to be an actor. Michael always gets rejected from many film productions because of his singing. Steve has a crush on an art director named Sara(who will be Steve's girlfriend at the end of the movie). Steve wishes that he could run his own film production and be like his father. His father was once a director and a producer but sadly died. He is frustrated with all of these sh***y movies like The Emoji Movie, Norm of the North, Ghostbusters(2016), the Transformers movies and etc. He learns about a time machine that was invented not to long ago. Steve eventually steals it. So Steve, Michael and Sara go on an adventure to stop the sh***y movies from being made. They also look back on many good movies from many companies like Disney and Dreamworks. Along the way, there being chased be many horrible directors like Michael Bay and Zach Snyder with there evil army of robots(robots made from SONY). Steve will also learn that things will happen and we need to accept it or ignore it. At the climax Michael Bay and Zachary Snyder will die from falling into a pit of lava. Since Steve went backed in time, it affected the space time continuum every single horrible movie never existed. Steve quits his job at SONY and runs his film production. Steve finale gets the girl. He also hires Michael to be an actor in his business. They continuously made a load of great movies. This eventually put SONY out of business. 

THE END 

"So kids the moral is to never make sh***y movie and accept the future."

Comment: The Emoji Movie is truly a work of art. It's truly so much deeper than what you see on the surface. The Emoji Movie shows us the terrors of a dystopian society that before this groundbreaking film, we weren't aware of. These emojis are forced to fit society's expectations for their entire lives, and we're abusing our power as the essential gods of the emoji universe. It's sad, but a truth that we need to face. Sony is the only company that's tried to spread awareness about this cause, one of the utmost importance, and for that, they should be respected as gods. I now spend hours worshipping Sony with my enlightened peers. Follow in my footsteps, ducklings. Learn the real horrors of our world and others, and spread this knowledge far and wide. Soon, all will know the true genius of the Emoji Movie.

Title: THE EMOJI MOVIE - Official Trailer (HD)
Comment: First of all the trailer spoils the whole story, which is bland and uninspired. So much so that I think I can write a better story right now by just making things up. I want to make a movie about a stick man. Like a literal stick man. Like he's made out of sticks. He randomly comes to be in the woods and some kids find him. He has human emotions and learns to talk and eventually starts going to school where (instead of the cliche bullying route where everyone makes fun of him for being different.) He fits in and everyone accepts him despite his uniqueness. But there will still be lots of opportunities for comedy as the stick man does not well understand human behaviors and is disposed to being highly environmental and always wanting to spend time outside. (Though the environmental messages will be troden on carefully and done subtly to avoid preachy fern gully/ James cameron avatar levels of we're drestroying the planet). Title: THE EMOJI MOVIE - Official Trailer (HD)
Comment:
I don't get all the hate on this movie. Someone please tell me 5 reasons to hate this movie. Beside the ones mentioned here.
Meanwhile, I'm going to try to disprove the most common hates on it.
1. Cliche: There really is nothing wrong with cliche. Some might say, "its overused", but that's exactly what cliche is, so explain what's wrong with overused. And it doesn't seem _that_ cliche, anyway.
2. Ripoff: lots of people say it's a ripoff of wreck it ralph and inside out. It really isn't, if you actually pay attention to the trailer. It's true that it has a similar concept to wreck it ralph, but the story isn't exactly the same like some might say. Emoji movie is a story of self discovery, who he is meant to be. Wreck it ralph isn't self discovery, it's a mix of redemption and accepting who you are. And honestly I don't get the relation to inside out. And also, at least it's not like a super cheap ripoff like Great Value off of everything(no offense, but seriously)
3. The Popeye movie: they didn't _popeye_ movie for this. They _delayed_ It. So stop spreading lies! And popeye movie is about an ordinary world, where all the rules are the practically the  same, but it has a guy with spinach powers. I would rather see a movie with a whole new undiscovered world where there's not much insight on what it's about.

Other things 
1. Animation is good
2. Story seems at least decent, not as bad as everyone following internet hate says it it.
3. Concept is interesting
4. Humor is meh... gonna be honest
5. Plot is creative and interesting

I know this comment may sound angry but I promise I'm not trying to be mad. And seriously, tell me more reasons why it's bad and why cliche is bad. Honestly I'm not that good of a movie analyzer (yes I know, the above is me analyzing the movie, but that stuff is obvious) so I just want to understand all the hate.

Title: THE EMOJI MOVIE - Official Trailer (HD)
Comment:
People are upset because Illumination, Sony, and possibly Dreamworks (which was bought by the owner of Illumination) could possibly be setting a trend in animated movies that is for the worse. Instead of creating movies that are thought provoking, beautiful, and have smart humor, these companies are turning to trends and relying on them for their movies rather than trying to create something timeless, which actually takes a lot of time and effort to do.

I personally am scared for the future of animated movies, as movies like these ones may seem simple and harmless, but they're creating more money than companies that actually try to bring quality entertainment, such as Laika and Disney. Secret Life of Pets, which is basically a horrid fusion of Toy Story and animal videos on YouTube, made 233.3 million more than Disney's Moana.

If these companies continue to make mediocre movies that do well in the box office, it's possible that the quality stories and actual effort we see in some animated movies today will completely relinquish, and these movies will rule over the animated movie genre. 

There is no heart put in to this film, the character designs took no effort at all because they're based on emojis, and the only reason it's being made is because emojis are what are "trendy" with the kids these days. Please, give us quality stories.

People experience emotional and mental health crises in response to a wide range of situations‚Äîfrom difficulties in their personal relationships to the loss of a job. For Veterans, these crises can be heightened by their experiences during military service. When emotional issues reach a crisis point, it‚Äôs time to call on the Veterans Crisis Line for support.

Sometimes a crisis may involve thoughts of suicide. Learn to recognize these warning signs:

Hopelessness, feeling like there‚Äôs no way out
Anxiety, agitation, sleeplessness, or mood swings
Feeling like there is no reason to live
Rage or anger
Engaging in risky activities without thinking
Increasing alcohol or drug abuse
Withdrawing from family and friends
The following signs require immediate attention:

Thinking about hurting or killing yourself
Looking for ways to kill yourself
Talking about death, dying, or suicide
Self-destructive behavior such as drug abuse, weapons, etc.
If you are a Veteran or know a Veteran who is experiencing any of these signs, call the Veterans Crisis Line immediately. Responders are standing by to help.

You can also learn to identify and understand risk factors for suicide.

Identifying the Signs

Many Veterans may not show any signs of intent to harm themselves before doing so, but some actions can be a sign that a Veteran needs help. Veterans in crisis may show behaviors that indicate a risk of harming themselves.

Learn more about how you can identify additional signs of suicide risk.

Take a Self-Check Quiz

Crisis, stress, depression, and other issues affect people in different ways. Maybe you‚Äôre having trouble sleeping or feel out of control. Maybe your energy level is down or you feel anxious all the time. If these issues and others seem to be leading to a crisis, treatment can help. Title: THE EMOJI MOVIE - Official Trailer (HD)
Comment:
Here's my list of complaints about this trailer:
1. It even exists.
2. This is literally just Wreck it Ralph. A character who has to play a specific role but wants to be more and ends up messing stuff up and going on an adventure with his friends.
3. 0:32 This freaking unfunny joke.
4. 1:02 This freaking hipster girl is wearing a winter scarf on a perfectly sunny day.
5. 1:15 What the heck kind of emoji is that. Bright hair beanie emoji? The heck is with that stupid pixel skull thing on it. 
6. The fact that this exists.
7. 1:20 A reference to an outdated meme. The creators seem to not realize that memes these days have very short life spans. Back in the mid 2000s, memes had very long life spans. Things like CDi cutscenes, Pepe the frog, those poorly drawn faces made to represent emotion, etc. Those were made at a time before things like "Behind the Meme," a channel which tries to introduce Normies to meme culture, but by doing that, makes memes have way shorter life spans, from 2 weeks to, at most, 2 months. 'Bye Felicia' may have been relevant when the script was made, but due to the creators' lack of knowledge on meme life spans, the movie is outdated before its even released. Imagine 20 years from now, the new generation wouldn't have a freaking clue what 'bye felicia' is. Sorry for going on this giant rant on meme life spans, but that scene made me genuinely want to punch a wall from how stupid it was.
8. 1:30 Making us endure 10 seconds of an unfunny joke.
9. The fact that the joke from number 8 will probably go on for longer than 10 seconds in the movie.
10. The fact that this exists for the third time.
11. 1:41 Forced love story.
12. 1:45 What the heck even is that. You mean to tell me that there are whales made of code in our phones? Or is this just a stupid impossibility made so there is a romantic scene.
13. 1:55 There is a Just Dance type game scene in this movie.
14. 1:59 Candy Crush.
15. 2:09 This unfunny joke.
16. The fact that this exists for the fourth flipping time.
17. THE.
18. FACT.
19. THAT.
20. THIS. 
21. EXISTS.
Overall score: üòÉüî´ / 10

Comment: Come on guys, cut the movie some slack, the story is as best as it can get, and people are trying their best to make it actually good. Don't you want to at least hope for the best? What if, it happens to be a decent movie? The cringe aspect of the whole setting will still exist, but at least they are trying to make it original and a little bit charming. Don't go into this movie with a mindset of trying to find the cringe, try to watch it from an actual storytelling and movie perspective. I am not trying to praise, I'm just saying put down the cringe for now, because we haven't seen the whole movie yet, and at least hope for a decent movie. If it's total cringe, then we can actually laugh, but right now it's not totally cringey. not without the fidget spinners.
